						<div class="abbv-col abbv-col-6">
							<div role="region" aria-label="USES"><h3>USES</h3>
<p><span style="background-color: transparent;">LINZESS<sup>®</sup> (linaclotide) is a prescription medication used to treat irritable bowel syndrome with constipation (IBS-C) in adults and in children and adolescents 7 years of age and older, chronic idiopathic constipation (CIC) in adults, and functional constipation (FC) in children and adolescents 6 years of age and older. “Idiopathic” means the cause of the constipation is unknown.<b> It is not known if LINZESS is safe and effective in children with functional constipation less than 6 years of age or in children with IBS-C less than 7 years of age.</b></span></p>
</div>

						</div>
						<div class="abbv-col abbv-col-6">
							<div role="region" aria-label="IMPORTANT RISK INFORMATION"><h2 class="safetybar-iri-text">IMPORTANT RISK INFORMATION</h2>
<ul>
<li><span style="background-color: transparent;"><b>Do not give LINZESS to children who are less than 2 years of age. It may harm them.</b> LINZESS can cause severe diarrhea and your child could get severe dehydration (loss of a large amount of body water and salt).</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: transparent;">Do not take LINZESS if a doctor has told you that you have a bowel blockage (intestinal obstruction).</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="linzess-isi-subtitle"><b>Before you take LINZESS, tell your doctor about your medical conditions, including if you are:</b></p>
</div>

						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
